{
  "texts": [
    "Second, it is very difficult to foresee the range of inputs that a full bottom-up AMA may possibly face.",
    "When training an image classifier, we can use images from many different positions, settings, types of lighting, etc., and be somewhat confident that this training set covers most of the space of potential images that the classifier may be presented with in the future.",
    "When we switch to the moral domain, however, there is a more significant possibility that future instances outrun the space covered by the training set.",
    "This is because moral behaviour takes place within a societal setting that is liable to rapid, often unforeseen, changes.",
    "Consider, for instance, the introduction of new technologies."
  ]
}